==English==
===Etymology===

* Old English '''hweogol''', '''hweol'''
* [[Proto-Indo-European]] '''*[[qwel]]''' ''going around'' 

Akin to:

* Old Norse '''hvel''' ''wheel'' 
* Greek '''kyklos''' ''circle, wheel''
* Latin '''colere''' ''to cultivate, inhabit'' 
* Sanskrit '''carati''' ''he moves, wanders''
* Old Korean '''huaet-gwi-et-gol''' (햇귀엣골), literally meaning, ''sun-rise ring''; or possibly '''huae-ui-gol''' (해의골) ''sun's ring, sun's halo''

